{
  "texts": [
    "All the datasets provided segmentation annotations by human experts, which have been widely used in existing literature (Supplementary Table 1 2 3 4).",
    "We incorporated these annotations directly for both model development and validation.",
    "The original 3D datasets consisted of computed tomography (CT) and magnetic resonance (MR) images in DICOM, nrrd, or mhd formats.",
    "To ensure uniformity and compatibility with developing medical image deep learning models, we converted the images to the widely used NifTI format.",
    "Additionally, grayscale images (such as X-Ray and Ultrasound) as well as RGB images (including endoscopy, dermoscopy, fundus, and pathology images), were converted to the png format."
  ]
}